  "notes": "Venda (Tshivenḓa) — Bantu language of South Africa and Zimbabwe, one of South Africa's official languages. The Latin orthography adds five under-dot/circumflex-below letters (ḓ ḽ ṋ ṱ) for the dental series contrasting with the alveolar d l n t, and ṅ for /ŋ/ (⟨ng⟩ being prenasalised /ŋɡ/). Plain ⟨p t k ts tsh ṱ pf⟩ write the ejective series; the ⟨h⟩ digraphs write the aspirated series. Five vowels /i ɛ a ɔ u/, with close-mid allophones. Venda is tonal, but tone is not marked in the standard orthography and no tone marks are emitted.",
